result.execSummary:
Nicholas Francis Techmeier was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Nicholas Francis Techmeier was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Nicholas Francis Techmeier in court, in custody.  Attorney Eric S. Maciolek appeared by phone.  Raymond L. Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Copy of Extradition Complaint given to Defendant. State advises of background of case. Court reviews Extradition Complaint, questions Defendant, who has reviewed his rights with Defense and does not request any additional time to speak with Defense.  Court questions Defense, who advises that Defendant wants to waive extradition.  Defendant wants to sign Waiver.  Court reviews consequences of signing Waiver, finds signature made freely and voluntarily.  Defendant questions whether there is a bond.  Court advises that bond is matter for Michigan Court.  Defendant signs waiver.  Court signs certification, questions whether an Order is prepared.  State advises there will not be a separate Order.  Court directs Sheriff's Dept. to notify State of Michigan.  State has nothing further.  Defense has nothing further.
